                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-205-victim1535 t18310630-205-viclabel1076"></join>, and live in Newman-street, Oxford-street. I employed the prisoner as a <rs id="t18310630-205-deflabel1077" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-205-defend1533 t18310630-205-deflabel1077"></join> about my house, and as a <rs id="t18310630-205-deflabel1078" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-205-defend1533 t18310630-205-deflabel1078"></join> in my shop - I <rs id="t18310630-205-viclabel1079" type="occupation">dealt in brokery</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-205-victim1535 t18310630-205-viclabel1079"></join>, but I have now sold off my stock; I saw at Mr. Shaves' shop, on the 10th of June, some shoes, which were part of my stock - I had missed shoes, and never gave the prisoner authority to pawn or sell them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-205-person1537">
                  JOHN 
                  SHAVE
               <interp inst="t18310630-205-person1537" type="surname" value="SHAVE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-205-person1537" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-205-person1537" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Union-street, Middlesex-hospital, and am a harness maker. The prisoner lodged in my house - he left in my debt; he agreed to pay me 5s. a week; he left, as security with me, nineteen duplicates and two boxes - one of the duplicates was for shoes, which were at Mr. Baxter's, and I took them out; I also bought of him a pair of child's boots on the 6th of May.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-205-person1538">
